NullPointerException is thrown when WaitCondition throws exception in method test() while WaitUntil is executing method wait(WaitCondition).

The problem is in logging. WaitUntil catches Exception thrown by WaitCondition.test() and try to log warning but the logger is null so it fails.

To reproduce this issue run this snippet:

``` java
new WaitUntil(new WaitCondition() {
            @Override
            public boolean test() {
                //throw some exception
                throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
            }
            @Override
            public String description() {
                return "Throws exception in method test()";
            }
        });
```

